Social</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe <a href=\"http:///www.capoeirastudio.com\" target=\"_blank\">Capoeira Studio</a> is full of accomplished people. We had doctors, lawyer, accountants, professors and even a couple of CEOs in our group. <a href=\"http://www.cdoseoul.com\" target=\"_blank\">CDO Seoul</a> is a comprised of a bunch of very busy Capoeira students. Most students want to just train and go home right after class. I understand that time is limited and that there is much to do. Training and going straight home is the easiest way to shorten your Capoeira life.<!--more-->\r\n\r\nOver the years I\'ve noticed that the students that really get Capoeira and are able to keep training for five or six years, or even more, know how to \"get social\". Those students that stick around after class or join other group activities are the ones that achieve <em>Capoeira longevity</em>.\r\n\r\nTo train Capoeira is to diligently prepare for a Capoeira game. How does a beginner do that? How does the newbie learn to play the game? How does the new Capoeirista learn how to prepare (diet, sleep, etc.) outside of class?\r\n\r\nThe dos and don\'ts of Capoeira are almost always discussed outside of class. Capoeira comes from an oral tradition. There is so much learning taking place outside of class room. Here are three easy ways to get social and learn more:\r\n<h5>Eat Together</h5>\r\nEating a delicious meal after class is easiest way to be more social with your Capoeira teacher and the group. Class time is for training. Meal time is the most appropriate time to delve into Capoeira philosophy with your teacher. It is also the perfect occasion to plan and discuss the annual batizado or the training curriculum. A tasty meal puts everyone in a good mood and makes it easier to deal with contentious issues that will often come up when your Capoeira teacher starts insisting that you wear white, come to class on time, and so on.\r\n<h5>Travel Together</h5>\r\nAttending group outings and traveling to distant Capoeira events as a group is the most efficient way to bond with the members of your group. At CDO Seoul, we have several overseas trips each year. Recently, we visited Hawaii, France, Japan and the USA. Popular group outings for CDO Seoul include our annual beach trip. Less time intensive outings include gathering for a good movie or a visit to an excellent sauna.\r\n\r\nMake every effort travel together. You will learn more about Capoeira and your group than you would if you simply attended classes for several months.\r\n<h5>Learn Together</h5>\r\nCapoeira groups usually have a Facebook Group or some other online forum for sharing information. Join the Facebook Group if there is one. It is essential for learning and getting to know the members of the group.\r\n\r\nThe Facebook Group is the forum where Capoeira videos are shared and discussed. Capoeira songs from the music class are posted there. Class rodas are often published there as well. This is forum where games are analyzed and discussed in detail.\r\n\r\nThe Facebook Group is often moderated by the teacher. So if you share posts about Capoeira there you can expect your teacher to respond and share their opinion with you. More importantly, it is a chance to get familiar with the other students. It is the resource to turn to if you are new to the group and forget your classmate\'s name!','Capoeira is Social','','publish','open','open','','capoeira-is-social','','','2015-12-23 04:43:31','2015-12-23 04:43:31','',0,'http://zumbicdo.quilombolaengineering.com/?p=51',0,'post','',0),(52,2,'2015-12-17 17:03:28','2015-12-17 17:03:28','<h3>3 Easy Ways To Get Social</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe <a href=\"http:///www.capoeirastudio.com\" target=\"_blank\">Capoeira Studio</a> is full of accomplished people. We had doctors, lawyer, accountants, professors and even a couple of CEOs in our group. <a href=\"http://www.cdoseoul.com\" target=\"_blank\">CDO Seoul</a> is a comprised of a bunch of very busy Capoeira 