 or a visit to an excellent sauna.\r\n\r\nMake every effort travel together. You will learn more about Capoeira and your group than you would if you simply attended classes for several months.\r\n<h5>Learn Together</h5>\r\nCapoeira groups usually have a Facebook Group or some other online forum for sharing information. Join the Facebook Group if there is one. It is essential for learning and getting to know the members of the group.\r\n\r\nThe Facebook Group is the forum where Capoeira videos are shared and discussed. Capoeira songs from the music class are posted there. Class rodas are often published there as well. This is forum where games are analyzed and discussed in detail.\r\n\r\nThe Facebook Group is often moderated by the teacher. So if you share posts about Capoeira there you can expect your teacher to respond and share their opinion with you. More importantly, it is a chance to get familiar with the other students. It is the resource to turn to if you are new to the group and forget your classmate\'s name!','Capoeira is Social','','inherit','closed','closed','','51-revision-v1','','','2015-12-17 17:03:28','2015-12-17 17:03:28','',51,'http://zumbicdo.quilombolaengineering.com/index.php/2015/12/17/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(53,2,'2015-03-05 17:04:07','2015-03-05 17:04:07','<h3>Three Reasons Why Capoeira Improves Intelligence</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWhat does walking on your hands have to do with intelligence? I\'d wager quite a lot. Apart from improving <a href=\"http://www.educlime.com/wharemosk.html\" target=\"_new\">motor skills</a>, the beautiful movements used in playing Capoeira help you to see the world differently. That new found perspective spills over into work and everyday life, giving you the creativity to address the multitude of challenges that we all must face everyday.\r\n\r\nHere are three reasons why Capoeira helps improve intelligence.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n<h5>Resourcefulness</h5>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nThe constraints of the <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E8hKh3NE-tw\" target=\"_new\">roda</a> (the circle in which a Capoeira game is played) mean that practitioners are constantly inventing new ways to move around. For example, people without Capoeira training want to escape an attack coming at them by moving backward. However, Capoeiristas (Capoeira practitioners) can\'t always move back to escape because of the restrictions the roda places upon their movement. Consequently, they are more aware that they can go over, under, or into an attack to evade the impending threat. This spills over into behavior at work and school. Capoeiristas are less likely to \"rely on the hammer\" and treat everything as a nail. Capoeiristas train themselves to be more resourceful.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n<h5>Creativity</h5>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nWalking on your hands really takes you out of your comfort zone as a biped. Being out of your comfort zone improves ones \"optimal performance zone\" according to Alasdair White\'s \"From Comfort Zone to Performance Management\" (2009). According to Jerry Wind (he teaches creativity at the prestigious <a href=\"http://www.wharton.upenn.edu/\" target=\"_new\">Wharton School</a> of Business), moving out of your comfort zone improves creativity. Capoeiristas routinely push out of their comfort zones. They develop a habit of performing optimally and living creatively.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n<h5>Imagination</h5>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nCapoeiristas often dream of moving differently at night when they sleep. This is a testimony to the fact that the art of Capoeira stimulates the imagination. The practice of Capoeira breaks down ingrained fears of failure and simultaneously replaces them with the belief that anything is possible. Once you start doing things you\'ve never done before with great frequency, as you do when you practice Capoeira, you increasingly question what is truly impossible. Capoeira 